  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of SVT-AV1</title>

    <para>
      Install SVT-AV1 by running the following commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>mkdir build &amp;&amp;
cd    build &amp;&amp;

cmake -D CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=/usr   \
      -D CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release    \
      -D CMAKE_SKIP_INSTALL_RPATH=ON \
      -D BUILD_SHARED_LIBS=ON        \
      -W no-dev -G Ninja .. &amp;&amp;

ninja</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      The test suite is very long and doesn't provide meaningful results. If
      you want to test the results anyway, issue:
    </para>

<screen remap='test'><userinput>cmake .. -D BUILD_TESTING=ON &amp;&amp;
ninja                        &amp;&amp;
ninja TestVectors            &amp;&amp;
SVT_AV1_TEST_VECTOR_PATH=$PWD/../test/vectors \
ctest -V -O testlog.txt --timeout 10800</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      On a relatively slow system, you may need to increase the timeout for
      the tests (see the SBU value for the tests on top of the page).  In the
      SvtAv1ApiTests test, 12 <literal>run_paramter<!--[sic]-->_check</literal>
      subtests are known to fail.  <!-- test/Readme.md mentions even more
      run_paramter_check failures so I guess those tests are just buggy. 

      I still get the 12 failures in SvtAv1ApiTests with version 4.0.0.
      The failing tests are named EncParam<something>Test.run_paramter_check.
        - bdubbs 2026-01-26
      -->
      The test harness will download a copy of libaom (even if
      <xref linkend='libaom'/> is already installed, the test harness is still
      unable to use the system installation) and some videos as test
      inputs.
    </para>

<!-- SVT-AV1's test suite clones into libaom and uses that test suite. After
     doing the test suite for libaom multiple times and generally having time
     wasted, there doesn't seem to be a good reason to do it here. Let's give
     the user the option and info needed to do it anyway, but not make it part
     of the standard measurements to save us time. - zeckma -->

    <para>
      Now, as the &root; user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>ninja install</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

